## Raw SQL (Use Sparingly)

### find_by_sql

```ruby
# Execute raw SQL
articles = Article.find_by_sql([
  "SELECT * FROM articles WHERE status = ? AND views_count > ?",
  'published',
  1000
])
```

### execute

```ruby
# Execute SQL without returning records
ActiveRecord::Base.connection.execute(
  "UPDATE articles SET views_count = views_count + 1 WHERE id = 1"
)
```

### sanitize_sql

```ruby
# Sanitize SQL to prevent injection
query = Article.sanitize_sql_array([
  "SELECT * FROM articles WHERE title LIKE ?",
  "%#{params[:search]}%"
])
```

